ng_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fee1-dead/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fee1-dead/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fee1-dead/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fee1-dead/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fee1-dead/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fee1-dead/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fee1-dead/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fee1-dead/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 7, "created_at": "2022-03-20T15:42:50Z", "updated_at": "2022-05-25T23:25:02Z", "closed_at": "2022-05-25T23:25:02Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Currently, `cargo run` has a big footgun: if you modify `src/bootstrap/bin/rustc.rs` (or rustdoc.rs), it won't be rebuilt until you manually run `cargo build --bins`. I tried avoiding this in https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/94828 by running that automatically in bootstrap, but it discards various linker arguments and environment variables that prevent people from configuring the build.\n\nA better solution is to introduce a binary that dispatches to different main functions, like rustup. If called as `bootstrap` it would run the main builder; if called as `rustc` or `rustdoc` it would run the logic currently in `rustc.rs` / `rustdoc.rs`; if called by any other name it should give a hard error.\n\ncc https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/94828#issuecomment-1066969753, https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/94829\n\nI am happy to help mentor this work.\n\n@rustbot label: +A-rustbuild +C-enhancement +E-mentor +E-help-wanted\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_START$${\"user\":\"fee1-dead\"}$$TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_END -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_END -->\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_END -->", 